{"article_id":"WQ7Rr7aECJtLIX53","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Nine California public school students are suing the state over its laws on teacher tenure , seniority and other protections","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"the plaintiffs say","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"keep bad educators in classrooms .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The case","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that goes to trial Monday in Los Angeles Superior Court","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"is the latest battle in a growing nationwide challenge to union-backed protections for teachers in an effort","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"to hold them more accountable for their work .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"The nonjury trial is expected to wrap up in March .","depth":3},{"id":9,"text":"`` The system is dysfunctional and arbitrary due to these outdated laws","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that handcuff school administrators , ''","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"said Theodore J. Boutrous , the lead attorney on the case","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"sponsored by an educational reform group .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"States across the nation have weakened teaching job protections ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"including generations-old tenure ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to give administrators more flexibility","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"to fire bad teachers .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Tenure was created in the early 20th century","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to prevent arbitrary or discriminatory firings","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"based on factors such as gender , nationality or political beliefs .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"It spelled out strict rules","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"under which teachers could be dismissed after a probationary period ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"though opponents claim","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"they make it virtually impossible to fire teachers","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"who are n't making the grade .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"The changes are occurring","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"as states replace virtually automatic `` satisfactory '' teacher evaluations with those","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"linked to teacher performance","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"and base teacher layoffs on performance instead of seniority .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Teachers ' unions are fighting back ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"the changes lower morale ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"deny teachers due process ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"and unfairly target older teachers .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"They also say","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"the evaluations are too dependent on standardized tests","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"and that eliminating such protections erases a vital support system for a profession","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"already losing talented people to higher paid private sector positions .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"The California Teachers Association and the California Federation of Teachers intervened","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"and asked the court to throw out the lawsuit","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"filed against the state ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"including the Department of Education , Gov . Jerry Brown and Superintendent of Public Education Tom Torlakson .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"`` It is deceptive and dishonest to pretend","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"that teacher due process rights are unfair to students , ''","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"said California Federation of Teachers President Josh Pechthalt , the parent of a ninth-grade student in the Los Angeles Unified School District .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"`` Students need a stable , experienced teaching workforce .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"They wo n't have one","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"if this lawsuit succeeds in gutting basic teacher rights . ''","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Judge Rolf Treu ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"who will decide the case ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"rejected a motion","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"to dismiss the case .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"The lawsuit wants the court to deem unconstitutional five statutes within the state education code .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Besides the one on tenure , three others lay out the steps","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to dismiss a teacher ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"and the fifth mandates the last-hired , first-fired rule ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"which","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"the lawsuit 's attorneys say","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"hurts teachers","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"who are young","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"but may be talented .","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"The plaintiffs are students primarily from the Los Angeles and Bay areas .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"They are supported by a nonprofit organization","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"called Students Matter","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"that says","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"it fights for education equality .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Los Angeles Unified School District Superintendent John Deasy ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"who oversees the nation 's second-largest school district ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"will be called to testify by the plaintiffs ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Boutrous said .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Plaintiff attorneys say","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"teachers too often get tenure","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"by just showing up for work","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"- after about 18 months in California .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Afterward , bad teachers are almost impossible or too expensive to fire ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"Boutrous said .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"`` The school system knowingly puts kids in classrooms with teachers","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"who are grossly substandard , ''","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"Boutrous said ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"that it was crucial to turn to the courts","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"because `` the political system ca n't fix this . ''","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"Many districts send substandard teachers to disadvantaged schools","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"instead of dismissing them","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"because those schools are seen as less desirable places","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"to work by experienced teachers ,","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"who can have priority","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"where they are assigned ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"Boutrous said .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"The California teacher unions say","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"they support improving teacher evaluations and streamlining the dismissal process .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"But those changes should be the work of the Legislature not the courts .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"Laura Lacar , a high school teacher in the ABC School District , fears","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"the law could expand beyond what happens in the classroom .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"`` It would be very scary to me ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"if this lawsuit succeeds ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"to think","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"that I might not have a job next year ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"not for anything","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"I 'd done in the classroom ,","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"but because my principal did n't like me , or my clothing , or something","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"I 'd said . ''","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"Declaring the laws unconstitutional will allow the Legislature to craft legislation","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"that does work ,","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"the lawsuit 's attorneys say .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"Karen Martinez ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"who lives in San Jose ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"her daughter , Daniella ,","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"who is a plaintiff ,","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"reached the third grade","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"unable to read","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"before a teacher helped her .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"`` I 'm hoping with all my heart","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"that we win this case ,","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"so California can change a system","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"that is clearly failing so many children , ''","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"Karen Martinez said .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"`` To me , it 's common sense :","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"appreciate and reward the teachers","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"who are doing great ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"and hold accountable the teachers","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"who are failing our kids . ''","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":124,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":125,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":126,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":127,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":128,"text":"Terry Moe , a senior fellow at Stanford University 's Hoover Institution","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"who has researched teacher unions and their impact on public education ,","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"said","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"there 's a long way to go even in states","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"that have adopted new laws .","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"`` Unions can make life difficult for administrators in coming years , ''","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"he said .","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"`` The political pressure on the ground is strong .","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"It 's going to be really difficult to follow through on these new laws","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"and put a dent in teacher tenure","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"and really do away with the role of seniority . ''","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":261,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":147,"right":260,"r